@realmoney Feb 05, 2020 | 11:35 AM EST DOUG KASS The Mouse Isn't Roaring Today * Despite its almost universal popularity, I would continue to avoid the shares of Disney Everyone loves Disney ($DIS) but the shares are weaker today (-$3.25/share) following the quarterly report.

Concerns I continue to have include the significant costs associated with content and the streaming service that lie ahead, park attendance and profitability, continued traditional broadcasting weakness and hard movie compares (year over year). Importantly, the implied value

(using conservative metrics for non streaming operations) of their streaming business is simply far too grand. I see lackluster absolute and relative EPS for the next 12 months at Disney. @cnbcfastmoney @ScottWapnerCNBC @terranovajoe
